ENTRY       EC 1.20.4.3                 Enzyme
NAME        mycoredoxin;
            Mrx1;
            MrxI
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on phosphorus or arsenic in donors;
            With disulfide as acceptor
SYSNAME     arseno-mycothiol:mycoredoxin oxidoreductase
REACTION    arseno-mycothiol + mycoredoxin = arsenite + mycothiol-mycoredoxin disulfide
SUBSTRATE   arseno-mycothiol;
            mycoredoxin
PRODUCT     arsenite [CPD:C06697];
            mycothiol-mycoredoxin disulfide
COMMENT     Reduction of arsenate is part of a defense mechanism of the cell against toxic arsenate. The substrate arseno-mycothiol is formed by EC 2.8.4.2 (arsenate:mycothiol transferase). A second mycothiol recycles mycoredoxin and forms mycothione.
